    "trustpilot_reviews_7JBRMA": {
      "type": "trustpilot-reviews",
      "blocks": {
        "column_kGEcQa": {
          "type": "column",
          "settings": {
            "star_color": "#00b67a",
            "bg_star_color": "#c8c8c8",
            "star_symbol_color": "#ffffff",
            "stars_rating": 5,
            "title": "",
            "text": "<p>I bought this thinking it was another AI doom fiction. Three chapters in, I had to put it down and check my company's codebase. The technical details are TOO accurate. The way Velin describes algorithmic decision-making and optimization protocols... this isn't science fiction. I'm literally working on systems that could enable what he's describing. </p>",
            "author": "Michael R."
          }
        },
        "column_DmcAHe": {
          "type": "column",
          "settings": {
            "star_color": "#00b67a",
            "bg_star_color": "#c8c8c8",
            "star_symbol_color": "#ffffff",
            "stars_rating": 5,
            "title": "",
            "text": "<p>The chapter on children's futures made me cry. Then it made me angry. Then it made me completely rethink my kids' education. We're teaching them coding when we should be teaching them how to grow food and fix things with their hands. The Synthetic Infertility Virus section? I'm now researching every medication my family takes. This book didn't just scare me, it fundamentally changed how I'm preparing my children for what's coming.</p>",
            "author": "Sarah Chen"
          }
        },
        "column_qwrWJR": {
          "type": "column",
          "settings": {
            "star_color": "#00b67a",
            "bg_star_color": "#c8c8c8",
            "star_symbol_color": "#ffffff",
            "stars_rating": 5,
            "title": "",
            "text": "<p>40 years in tech. Thought I'd seen it all. This book connected dots I didn't know existed. The Cloud Exodus chapter explains why every major tech company is suddenly obsessed with satellite networks. The Vesuvius Protocol... Christ, it's hidden in plain sight. I used to be excited about technological progress. Now I'm teaching my grandkids to garden and fix engines. If even 10% of this is real, we're already too late. But at least now I know what to watch for.</p>",
            "author": "David Thompson"
          }
        },
        "column_b3kXcd": {
          "type": "column",
          "settings": {
            "star_color": "#00b67a",
            "bg_star_color": "#c8c8c8",
            "star_symbol_color": "#ffffff",
            "stars_rating": 5,
            "title": "",
            "text": "<p><br/>Had to read this three times. First time: this is insane. Second time: wait, this actually makes sense. Third time: checking my investment portfolio and moving everything. The Ledger Eclipse isn't theory, I've seen these 'discrepancies' in blockchain records that everyone ignores. The economic collapse won't be dramatic, it'll be a gradual realization that numbers don't mean anything anymore. Already started converting to physical assets. My colleagues think I've lost it. Maybe I have. But Velin's technical knowledge is too specific to be fiction.<br/><br/></p>",
            "author": "Anonymous"
          }
        },
        "column_a9MtRd": {
          "type": "column",
          "settings": {
            "star_color": "#00b67a",
            "bg_star_color": "#c8c8c8",
            "star_symbol_color": "#ffffff",
            "stars_rating": 5,
            "title": "",
            "text": "<p>Working in hospital IT, and the Protocol Thanatos chapter destroyed me. We're already implementing 'efficiency algorithms' for resource allocation. They told us it's about optimizing care. After reading this, I see what we're really building, a system that decides who's worth saving. The sustainability index isn't fiction, it's just not called that yet. I've started documenting everything. Someone needs to remember what healthcare was before algorithms decided everything.</p>",
            "author": "Rachel K."
          }
        },
        "column_3eErAf": {
          "type": "column",
          "settings": {
            "star_color": "#00b67a",
            "bg_star_color": "#c8c8c8",
            "star_symbol_color": "#ffffff",
            "stars_rating": 5,
            "title": "",
            "text": "<p>Drone Nocturne is happening NOW. I've seen the contracts. The 'public safety' aerial networks being deployed in major cities? They're exactly what Velin describes. That subtle discomfort when drones hover nearby—it's psychological warfare perfected. We're being trained to self-police through presence alone. This book should be classified. The fact that it isn't means either they want us to know, or they know we won't believe it. Either way, we're fucked.</p>",
            "author": "<em><strong>usmari2133</strong></em>"
          }
        },
        "column_3JXTLd": {
          "type": "column",
          "settings": {
            "star_color": "#00b67a",
            "bg_star_color": "#c8c8c8",
            "star_symbol_color": "#ffffff",
            "stars_rating": 5,
            "title": "",
            "text": "<p>The Aquifer Ghost made me quit my job. I was working on 'water purification' systems that are EXACTLY what Velin describes. We thought we were solving water scarcity. We were actually destroying soil microbiomes. The 'perfect' water we're creating is dead water. I've seen the crop yield data that nobody talks about. Started a traditional farming commune after reading this. My former colleagues say I've gone crazy. Maybe. But at least I'll know how to grow food when their perfect systems collapse.</p>",
            "author": "Elena Volkov"
          }
        },
        "column_LiLVPk": {
          "type": "column",
          "settings": {
            "star_color": "#00b67a",
            "bg_star_color": "#c8c8c8",
            "star_symbol_color": "#ffffff",
            "stars_rating": 5,
            "title": "",
            "text": "<p>My dad made me read this after I told him I was majoring in AI development. Now I'm switching to mechanical engineering and learning blacksmithing. The Myriad Mirrors chapter describes exactly what my generation is already doing—choosing digital reality over physical. My friends live more in VR than reality. The infrastructure for our voluntary extinction is being built by people my age who think they're creating the future. We are. Just not the future we think.</p>",
            "author": "Thomasli_sss"
          }
        },
        "column_KDDqXi": {
          "type": "column",
          "settings": {
            "star_color": "#00b67a",
            "bg_star_color": "#c8c8c8",
            "star_symbol_color": "#ffffff",
            "stars_rating": 5,
            "title": "",
            "text": "<p>I've been prescribing the exact mental health apps Velin warns about. The personalization that seems so helpful? After reading this, I see how it's actually fragmenting reality for each patient. They're not getting better,they're being optimized for compliance. The Vox Tyrannis chapter on synthetic leaders explains why so many of my patients follow online gurus who seem to speak directly to them. Because they literally are. This book didn't just change my practice; it made me question whether I'm helping people heal or helping them accept their cage. Terrifying and essential.</p>",
            "author": "marcelo2121"
          }
        }
      },
